node.statement: PROOF NOT FOUND via Herglotz. omega_1 is an algebraic function (branch of degree-n curve), NOT Nevanlinna-class rational. Im(omega_1(z)) < Im(z) possible, so phi=omega_1-id is not Herglotz; Nevanlinna representation gives phi'>0 everywhere, contradicting phi'(nu_k)=0. APPROACH DEFINITIVELY BLOCKED. KEY NEW FINDINGS: (1) Cauchy matrix identity: <h,alpha> = sum_{k<l} (h_k-h_l)(phi_k-phi_l)/[(nu_k-nu_l)(lambda_k-lambda_l)] with positive weights but mixed-sign numerators (92% positive, 8% negative). (2) <h,alpha>>=0 fails 71% for random (non-MSS) pairs, confirming MSS structure essential. (3) F(t)=<h_r,h_t> along interpolation x(t)=(1-t)nu+t*lambda satisfies F(t)>=F(0) (0/500 violations) -- this IS <h,alpha>>=0. (4) Phi(t)=||h_t||^2 always monotone increasing (Schur-concavity + majorization gives weaker Phi_r<=Phi_p). PROMISING DIRECTIONS: (A) Prove F(t)>=F(0) via barrier argument at contact points. (B) Use Cauchy decomposition + MSS coefficient structure. See proof_h_alpha_herglotz.md for full writeup.
